	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				----------------------------------------------<BR>
<BR>
Here are the four items you need to turn in to obtain the red headband:<BR>
<BR>
Head of Ghanex Drah<BR>
Skull of Brother Denab<BR>
Head of Brother Shen<BR>
Your Orange Headband<BR>
<BR>
Item locations:<BR>
Head of Ghanex Drah is found on Ghanex Drah, a necromancer (17'ish) found in South Karana by the undead camp(very north end of the zone, near the stone bridge).<BR>
<BR>
Skull of Brother Denab is found on High Shaman Phido(18'ish) who will spawn somewhere in South Karana.<BR>
<BR>
Head of Brother Shen is found on High Shaman Grisok (18'ish) who will also spawn somewhere in South Karana.<BR>
<BR>
How to get the High Shaman's to spawn:<BR>
I never really timed the spawn after killing one or the other, however, somewhere in the zone there can be up to two regular gnoll shamans, Shaman Lenrel and Shaman Ren`Rex. You need to kill BOTH of these shamans to have a chance at one or the other of the High Shamans to spawn, as they are placeholders. Both of the regular shaman's may or may not be up at the same time, however, once you have killed both, then there is a chance of one of the High Shamans spawning.<BR>
<BR>
Side Note:<BR>
In the 9 hours I spent in South Karana, I got High Shaman Phido about a dozen times, and High Shaman Grisok only once. However, the one time I killed High Shaman Grisok, High Shaman Phido spawned IMMEDIATELY upon Grisok's death. I am not sure if this was coincidence of by design. Just thought I would mention it.<BR>
<BR>
I also suggest taking a tracker to assist you, as any one of these four NPC's can spawn anywhere in the zone, which makes it a pain to find them. =)<BR>
<BR>
The information I have provided here is FACT. I did this over a 9 hour period in South Karana on Saturday 03/24/01.<BR>
<BR>
If you have any questions, feel free to drop me an email!<BR>
<BR>
Lydola Golightly<BR>
55 Beguiler - Veeshan<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
